[
    {
        "content": "<p>Bonjour!<br>\nI want to write a program that can index into the fibonnaci number sequence, but as it turns out, they quickly get larger than even a U128. I know there aren't BigInt-s in the standard library or language for a good reason, but that begs the question, how do you recommend I make my custom version for this program to work?</p>\n<p>I basically need a data type with lenght I can define. The two options that come to mind are Str and List(U128) with some custom definition of a function to become my + operator.</p>\n<p>Do you see another option and what do you recommend?<br>\nAlso, while I'm at it, is Dec a true decimal number or basically something like F64 ?</p>\n<p>Thanks in advance 'x)</p>",
        "id": 601749816,
        "sender_full_name": "TheoTheTorch",
        "timestamp": 1781089905
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi Theo :)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Dec a true decimal number or basically something like F64 ?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Dec is a true decimal and will avoid the typical float issues.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>with some custom definition of a function to become my + operator.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>By the way, if you make a function named <code>plus</code> on your type, it will just work with <code>+</code>.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Do you see another option and what do you recommend?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I would recommend using a <code>List(64)</code> so that for addition you can convert them to U128 and the result will fit guaranteed.</p>",
        "id": 601763012,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1781092865
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, you'll be able to write tests for it easily, because we have special \"constructors\" for number literals.<br>\nYou don't need to do <code>MyBigNum.new(1)</code>. You can just do <code>1</code> if MyBigNum implements the appropriate methods. I don't know where it's discussed, but this is the first msg i have found that mentions them (it's the from digits method):<br>\n<a href=\"#narrow/channel/395097-compiler-development/topic/number.20type.20inference/near/556715492\">https://roc.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/395097-compiler-development/topic/number.20type.20inference/near/556715492</a></p>",
        "id": 601774573,
        "sender_full_name": "Norbert Hajagos",
        "timestamp": 1781095169
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"1082352\">@TheoTheTorch</span> check out <a href=\"https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/185a692980d8d85fb06960aad25d1510cd30d450/docs/langref/numbers.md#custom-number-types\">https://github.com/roc-lang/roc/blob/185a692980d8d85fb06960aad25d1510cd30d450/docs/langref/numbers.md#custom-number-types</a></p>",
        "id": 601787855,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1781097575
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>it's not merged yet but that should explain - lmk if you have questions about it!</p>",
        "id": 601787902,
        "sender_full_name": "Richard Feldman",
        "timestamp": 1781097584
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Oh wow I am reading that right away!</p>",
        "id": 601788636,
        "sender_full_name": "TheoTheTorch",
        "timestamp": 1781097713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You guys were not kidding about the friendly part :')</p>",
        "id": 601788695,
        "sender_full_name": "TheoTheTorch",
        "timestamp": 1781097725
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Hey, I got stuck on figuring out how I can instantiate a type I am defining. Also, I am guessing a nominal type is better for something like this than an opaque type?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">Bigbig</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">List</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">U64</span><span class=\"p\">).{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">plus</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_b</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TODO</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">minus</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_b</span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">TODO</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_numeral</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Numeral</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">([</span><span class=\"n\">Bigbig</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">],</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">InvalidNumeral</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">..</span><span class=\"p\">])</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">from_numeral</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"n\">literal</span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">match</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">U64</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">from_numeral</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">literal</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nb\">Err</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">InvalidNumeral</span><span class=\"p\">())</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"n\">Try</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">List</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">))</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>from_numaral : Numeral -&gt; Try([List(U64), ..], [InvalidNumeral, ..])<br>\ninstead of what I want it to be.</p>",
        "id": 601808360,
        "sender_full_name": "TheoTheTorch",
        "timestamp": 1781101320
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>opaque is better actually!</p>",
